The paper deals with the theory of codes and their properties, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of affine geometries and their connection to toric codes suggests a possible fit under Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses collections of lines and subsets, which are concepts in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The study of minimum distance and heuristic searches for good codes falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the lattice geometry of exponent vectors, which is a topic in Graph Theory (cs.GT).
